  "title": {
    "en": "Eternal Life and Glory"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "Before his arrest, Jesus looked toward heaven and prayed.",
      "His prayer revealed his mission and his relationship with the Father."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "authority",
        "icon": "public",
        "label": { "en": "Authority to Give Life" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus prayed,",
          "“Father, the time has come.",
          "Glorify your Son,",
          "that your Son may glorify you.",
          "You granted him authority over all people,",
          "that he might give eternal life",
          "to all those you have given him.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "eternal_life",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "What Is Eternal Life?" },
        "lines": [
          "“Now this is eternal life:",
          "that they may know you,",
          "the only true God,",
          "and Jesus Christ,",
          "whom you have sent.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "glory",
        "icon": "auto_awesome",
        "label": { "en": "Before the World Began" },
        "lines": [
          "“I have brought you glory on earth",
          "by completing the work you gave me to do.",
          "And now, Father,",
          "glorify me in your presence",
          "with the glory I had with you",
          "before the world began.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Jesus speaks of knowing the only true God, and of sharing glory before the world began. What do these words suggest about his identity and mission?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 17:1–5"]
  }
}
